@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"You have no power over me."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubrimose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 8:48:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1181.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My top 5 decisions for race/class/deity:</span><hr size=1> Hey, this is a roleplay server.  Since you will need to be in character most of the time, pick the combo that will keep you most intersted in your character.  For some, that means picking something that is almost exactly like them in rl, and for others that means picking something that is almost the exact opposite of their rl self.  I chose the first of these two choices, going with a human ranger of Tunare.  Definitely not many of us out there, and definitely a combo that most uber players would say &quot;What the hell were you thinking man?&quot; but it's the one that made the most sense to me as far as staying in character and having the most fun.<br><br>That being said, I agree with the consensus of human Bertoxx cleric, if you're able to pull it off... that could be really really fun! <p>Brimose Greymyst <BR>25 Ranger of the Glade, Nameless of Mercy on The Nameless, semi-retired <BR>Brion (Raydon) <BR>14 Ranger of the Glade, Elder, Treasurer, and Charter Member of the Clan of Brothers on Fironia Vie <BR>Leaving my mark all over Norrath... in corpses <BR>Ack!  Ranger Down!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 9:12:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1181.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My top 5 decisions for race/class/deity:</span><hr size=1> as much as I agree that the Bertoxxulous cleric seems like a fun choice..... in the end, I want to see her play whatever SHE feels will provide the most enjoyment for her. <br><br>I retract my previous statements.... because in the end, the only advice I have for her is:  <br><br>&quot;Play whatever you want, play what you feel is fun for you, not what others think. Never choose a character because other people nudged you into that choice.&quot;<br><br>And also.... don't feel guilty about starting over. A lot of people in this forum have done it in this server (re-roll their characters).  If you have to keep restarting characters until you get &quot;the perfect one&quot;..... then do it. Never feel guilty about it.  <br><br>In the end, all that matters is that you feel comfortable with your character.... because we spend so much time in this game that our characters become our real avatars.... they are an extension of ourselves, there is a part of us in these characters, sometimes it's not so obvious. And sometimes it takes trial and error before we find the perfect match. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upogel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pogel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 1:01:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1181.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My top 5 decisions for rac